    "evt_aidar90s_bankruptcy_trigger_msg" to "The money has run out. Inflation has finished off.",
    "evt_aidar90s_parents_scam_again_conditional_opt_stop_parents_hard" to "Block their accounts (Hard)",
    "evt_aidar90s_parents_scam_again_conditional_opt_let_them_try" to "Let them learn on their own (Dangerous)",
    "evt_aidar_2005_intro_msg" to "Spring 2005. Aidar leaves the old Internet cafe on Abai and holds his first salary in his pocket. The banknotes are warm, as if they had just been printed, but the fans of the system units and the words of the boss are still noisy in my head: “If you move, you will grow faster than others.”\n\nHe lives with his mother and younger brother in a cramped apartment, commutes halfway across town to work and pretends to be calm. In fact, he is scared: oil is pumping up the economy, his friends are grabbing loans, people are talking about “easy money”, and all he knows so far is how to fix other people’s websites at night.\n\nThe account is {capital}. Income {income} per month. After expenses, there is too little left for error, but right now a friend is calling for a small trading scheme with phones, and the family is waiting for Aidar to be the first to get them out of the constant shortage.",
    "evt_aidar_2005_intro_opt_help_brother" to "First help brother with family preparations and expenses",
    "evt_aidar_2005_intro_opt_save_first" to "Hide the money in an envelope and think only about your growth",
    "evt_aidar_2005_startup_pitch_msg" to "Sayakhata smells of dust, gasoline and chance. An old classmate, Timur, shows a trunk full of push-button telephones: “We take a batch, put it point by point, the profit for a month will be the same as your six-month salary.”\n\nAidar wants to stop counting change in front of the cash register for the first time. But he also sees something else: there is no paper, the agreement is only in words, and the market rests on someone else’s confidence and his ability not to blink first.\n\nYou can enter with money, time, or not enter at all. The price of the decision for him is not only profit: if he makes a mistake, the family will find out that their “hope” is still the same boy as he was.",
    "evt_aidar_2005_startup_pitch_opt_join_startup" to "Enter with money and take the risk",
    "evt_aidar_2005_startup_pitch_opt_partial_startup" to "Help with code and logistics, but don't invest savings",
    "evt_aidar_2005_startup_pitch_opt_skip_startup" to "Give up and stay in the craft",
    "evt_aidar_2005_startup_3months_msg" to "For three months Aidar sees almost no daylight. Work during the day, announcements at night, tables, resales, calls. Money flashes faster than it can become peace of mind.\n\nTimur is already speaking like a man from the future: a second warehouse, his own website, direct deliveries. Aidar feels that fatigue is turning into excitement, and excitement will soon cease to distinguish the border between courage and greed.\n\nNow you can either record the result and return to your career, or go even deeper into the scheme and connect the next year of your life with it.",
    "evt_aidar_2005_startup_3months_opt_pitch_investors" to "Stay in business and pump the scheme stronger",
    "evt_aidar_2005_startup_3months_opt_exit_startup" to "Leave with what you managed to save",
    "evt_aidar_2005_startup_result_msg" to "In the fall, the market cools down as sharply as it warmed up. At two points the cash register has sank, the supplier demands an advance payment, and Timur speaks in a whisper for the first time. In the room where growth was recently discussed, they are now counting who is owed and how much.\n\nAidar understands an unpleasant thing: fast money always wants you to attach your name to it. If you leave suddenly now, you can save your reputation and part of your capital. If you stay, there is a chance to pull out the project, but the cost of a mistake will become personal.\n\nThe decision is no longer about courage. It's about growing up: turning a blind eye to risk or recognizing that a beautiful story doesn't have to become destiny.",
    "evt_aidar_2005_startup_result_opt_strong_pitch" to "Take control and save the case",
    "evt_aidar_2005_startup_result_opt_safe_exit" to "Close the story and return to the profession",
    "evt_aidar_2005_senior_promotion_msg" to "The office smells of cheap coffee and soldering iron. The boss looks at Aidar over the monitor for a long time, then nods: “The sites are based on you. We can lift you up, but we need to stop being a help boy.”\n\nThis is not the glossy career path they write about in magazines. These are long evenings, other people's mistakes, difficult customers and the feeling that professionalism is born here without fanfare, almost in silence.\n\nA promotion will give you more air, but also more responsibility. At the same time, an acquaintance is calling for a freelance project, which could open a new trajectory if Aidar can withstand double the load.",
    "evt_aidar_2005_senior_promotion_opt_middle_promo" to "Get promoted and build a name within the company",
    "evt_aidar_2005_senior_promotion_opt_senior_astana" to "Move into a more daring market and seek growth through new projects",
    "evt_aidar_2005_senior_promotion_opt_stay_same" to "Stay in the shadows for a while longer and observe",
    "evt_aidar_2015_intro_msg" to "Summer 2015. Almaty seems more modern than it was yesterday: coworking spaces, coffee shops, startup meetups, endless conversations about applications. Aidar is no longer the student of his dreams, but a developer who finally feels that he can choose his own life.\n\nBut under the smooth city window something is trembling. The tenge is unstable, friends are transferring their savings into dollars, some are leaving, others are taking out loans because “later it will be too late.” Aidar is twenty-four, and they expect from him not just ambitions, but adult decisions.\n\nHe has {capital} in his account, {income} per month and the feeling that one precise move can sharply lift him up. Mom is still counting on helping the family, and a former classmate calls on him to build a product that will “blow up the market.”",
    "evt_aidar_2015_intro_opt_help_brother" to "First, consolidate the family and take on some of their anxiety",
    "evt_aidar_2015_intro_opt_save_first" to "Collect the pillow and not spill the chance for growth",
    "evt_aidar_2015_startup_pitch_msg" to "In the coffee shop, Daniyar’s eyes light up as if he has already seen the future. He lays out the napkins like a presentation: marketplace for local artists, export, Astana Hub, angels, first round, rapid growth.\n\nAidar listens and notices a familiar feeling. He is drawn not only to money. He is drawn to a version of himself who is not afraid of the big game. But this is precisely what scares us the most: sometimes a dream sounds so convincing that you stop asking it tough questions.\n\nYou can enter with capital, work or a beautiful refusal. Each of these roles is honest in its own way. The only question is who Aidar is ready to be now.",
    "evt_aidar_2015_startup_pitch_opt_join_startup" to "Invest money and really get into the startup",
    "evt_aidar_2015_startup_pitch_opt_partial_startup" to "Help the product with your hands without risking all your capital",
    "evt_aidar_2015_startup_pitch_opt_skip_startup" to "Stay in a stable career and don't buy other people's confidence",
    "evt_aidar_2015_startup_3months_msg" to "Three months dissolve in nightly meetings, meetings and lack of sleep. The MVP is already alive, the masters are coming, the first orders are more pleasing than the annual bonus. And yet, behind every small success lies the long shadow of the question: will it be enough when the euphoria ends.\n\nAidar started talking about the product in the plural. This is a dangerous moment. When you begin to build the future with the voice of “we,” failure ceases to be just a financial mistake and becomes a personal shame.\n\nDaniyar insists on pitching to investors. Aidar understands: either they are now taking a step towards real business, or this whole story will remain a beautiful youth, for which they paid with sleep and money.",
    "evt_aidar_2015_startup_3months_opt_pitch_investors" to "Go all the way and pitch",
    "evt_aidar_2015_startup_3months_opt_exit_startup" to "Get out now and take what you can salvage",
    "evt_aidar_2015_startup_result_msg" to "It's cold and too bright in Astana Hub. Investors look as if they already know the answer, and Aidar feels for the first time how knowledge of the code and knowledge of money diverge in different directions. Putting the product together turned out to be easier than explaining why you should believe in it.\n\nHe notices a strange duality in himself. One part of him wants to show off, to prove that he didn’t live these sleepless months in vain. The other wants to leave the room and choose a life where you don’t have to look more confident than you are every day.\n\nNext will be either a grant and a new level of pressure, or an honest return to your career. Both outcomes change Aidar. Just in different directions.",
    "evt_aidar_2015_startup_result_opt_strong_pitch" to "Talk tough and take a chance to grow",
    "evt_aidar_2015_startup_result_opt_safe_exit" to "Stop before ambition eats away your support",
    "evt_aidar_2015_startup_success_msg" to "They liked it. Real money appears on the table, and there are immediately no free days left on the calendar. Everything that was a dream suddenly turns into work: calls, reports, other people's expectations, new obligations.\n\nAidar feels euphoria, but not peace. When a dream finally happens, sometimes the first thing that comes is not happiness, but heaviness. Now he has a chance to become a man who builds his own. And there is a risk of losing health and simple life before the product grows.\n\nYou need to decide what he will give to the startup: only energy after his main job or his entire career.",
    "evt_aidar_2015_startup_success_opt_quit_job" to "Quit your job and put everything on the product",
    "evt_aidar_2015_startup_success_opt_keep_job" to "Leave work and carry on two fronts at once",
    "evt_aidar_2015_senior_promotion_msg" to "A few months later, Aidara is called by the team lead. There is no pathos in the voice, only businesslike directness: he was noticed. At the same time, an offer came from Astana, more dramatic in terms of money and louder in status.\n\nIn 2015, it's no longer just a matter of career. This is a question of currency, future expenses, rented housing, the possibility of someday buying your own. One solution seems reasonable. The other looks like a leap into the next version of yourself.\n\nAidar needs to choose where he wants to grow up: inside a known system or in a space where growth is paid for with nerves, travel and the risk of making mistakes louder than usual.",
    "evt_aidar_2015_senior_promotion_opt_middle_promo" to "Stay and grow within the team",
    "evt_aidar_2015_senior_promotion_opt_senior_astana" to "Go to Astana for a big step",
    "evt_aidar_2015_senior_promotion_opt_stay_same" to "Wait and don’t waste yourself on fuss",
    "evt_aidar_2024_intro_msg" to "Almaty, 2024. At every meetup they talk about AI, productivity, options and their own products. Aidar already has a normal job, a better laptop than half of his teachers once had, and a strange feeling that the market has accelerated faster than he had time to get used to as an adult.\n\nFrom the outside he looks put together. Inside, everything is more complicated: the family still asks for help, colleagues suddenly quit for startups, and the news feed hints every day that if you don’t take a risk now, you can forever remain just a “good performer.”\n\nAccount {capital}, income {income} per month. This is no longer poverty, but not yet freedom. And that’s why every decision becomes more dangerous: it hurts more to make mistakes when you have something to lose.",
    "evt_aidar_2024_intro_opt_help_brother" to "Put your family ahead of your pace and take on some of their workload",
    "evt_aidar_2024_intro_opt_save_first" to "Build yourself a foothold before saving everyone else",
    "evt_aidar_2024_startup_pitch_msg" to "A friend invites you not just to a startup, but to the “right wave”: an AI service for small businesses, a rapid prototype, angel money, pilots with real companies. Everything sounds so modern that refusal almost seems like a sign of cowardice.\n\nBut Aidar is old enough to notice how fashion can mask dampness. He understands the product, but does not fully understand unit economics. And this is the same crack through which money often flows out of dreams.\n\nYou can go deep, you can limit yourself to a technical role, you can stay employed and observe from the sidelines. Each option will preserve something important and deprive something equally important.",
    "evt_aidar_2024_startup_pitch_opt_join_startup" to "Invest money and become a co-founder for real",
    "evt_aidar_2024_startup_pitch_opt_partial_startup" to "Login as a tech lead without a full financial jump",
    "evt_aidar_2024_startup_pitch_opt_skip_startup" to "Stay employed and don’t burn your support for the sake of hype",
    "evt_aidar_2024_startup_3months_msg" to "Three months later, the product has its first customers, but there is no feeling of victory. There are metrics that can be beautifully shown in a presentation, and there is a team that is already tired before it gets rich.\n\nAidar wakes up at night and does not immediately remember where he is going in the morning: to the office or to the next rescue mode. He begins to understand that adult risk differs from youth risk not in the size of the bet, but in the number of people you pull with you.\n\nHe has a choice again. Add the story to the next round or regain your right to normal sleep and a predictable life.",
    "evt_aidar_2024_startup_3months_opt_pitch_investors" to "Finish the round and prove that everything is not in vain",
    "evt_aidar_2024_startup_3months_opt_exit_startup" to "Stop and save yourself",
    "evt_aidar_2024_startup_result_msg" to "At a meeting with the foundation, the questions turn out to be more mature than the project itself. Not “how beautiful”, but “how much does the client cost”, “when will you pay off”, “who will stay if sales decline.” This is no longer a game of imaginary futures. This is a test of whether you can live in reality.\n\nAidar suddenly feels better than expected. Not because he's confident. Because he finally sees the project without a romantic filter. This is a rare and precious moment of clarity.\n\nIf he steps on the gas now, the startup will become the center of his life. If he retreats, he will not feel like a coward, because he will understand the cost of conscious refusal.",
    "evt_aidar_2024_startup_result_opt_strong_pitch" to "Take the chance and don't look away",
    "evt_aidar_2024_startup_result_opt_safe_exit" to "Choose adult distance over beautiful chaos",
    "evt_aidar_2024_startup_success_msg" to "The round happened. Congratulations are given in chats, the investor writes “let’s go,” the team gets salaries and KPIs. On the outside, everything looks like success.\n\nInside, Aidar suddenly feels not triumph, but a lack of air. Now this is not just a product that can be closed without explanation. Now it's structure, contracts, people, expectations and an almost constant feeling that he lives on the edge of his own attention.\n\nHe needs to decide how he will carry this success: will he completely go into it or try to leave at least one support outside the business.",
    "evt_aidar_2024_startup_success_opt_quit_job" to "Burn bridges and go completely to the company",
    "evt_aidar_2024_startup_success_opt_keep_job" to "Hold two supports and pay for it with fatigue",
    "evt_aidar_2024_senior_promotion_msg" to "Recruiters are already writing as if they know Aidar better than he does: remote teams, salaries in foreign currency, options, a new stack, promotion to technical lead. At the same time, the current company offers a noticeable step up and promises “stable development.”\n\nIn 2024, stability sounds almost exotic. Everything around teaches that the one who is faster wins. But Aidar already knows the price of speed: it often comes complete with anxiety, blurred boundaries and a constant feeling that you have to be better than your fatigue.\n\nHe chooses not just a salary. He chooses what kind of adult life he will explain to himself for the next few years.",
    "evt_aidar_2024_senior_promotion_opt_middle_promo" to "Grow within the current team and strengthen the base",
    "evt_aidar_2024_senior_promotion_opt_senior_astana" to "Accept a more daring offer and speed up sharply",
    "evt_aidar_2024_senior_promotion_opt_stay_same" to "Take a break and don't buy an extra race",
    "evt_aidar_2024_freelance_order_msg" to "A former client writes late at night: we need an urgent project, the money is normal, the deadlines are unpleasant. This is the same extra income that looks beautiful in the table and is hard to experience in life.\n\nAidar knows his weakness: it is difficult for him to refuse a chance that looks like another floor up. But each such floor is built from hours, which he almost no longer has.\n\nYou can take an order for the sake of money and experience, you can honestly overestimate the deadlines, you can refuse and keep the strength for yourself.",
    "evt_aidar_2024_freelance_order_opt_freelance_yes" to "Take the entire order and make the most of the month",
    "evt_aidar_2024_freelance_order_opt_freelance_half" to "Narrow down the volume and don’t burn yourself out",
    "evt_aidar_2024_freelance_order_opt_freelance_no" to "Give up and keep the pace",
    "evt_aidar_2024_family_pressure_msg" to "Mom calls late. Her voice always becomes quieter when talking about money. My brother needs help, my father has health problems again, no one dramatizes out loud at home, but all the anxiety still somehow comes to Aidar.\n\nHe loves them and hates this feeling at the same time. Because every transfer to a family is not just an expense. This is also a silent promise that he will withstand everything, even if he himself is still barely building his stability.\n\nThe account is {capital}. You can help in different ways, but not a single option will allow you to remain completely innocent either in front of them or in front of yourself.",
    "evt_aidar_2024_family_pressure_opt_help_fully" to "Solve the problem with money completely",
    "evt_aidar_2024_family_pressure_opt_help_partial" to "Help only with the most urgent part",
    "evt_aidar_2024_family_pressure_opt_help_minimum" to "To be honest, you can't stand it anymore",
    "evt_aidar_2024_mortgage_offer_msg" to "The bank sends preliminary approval. A rented apartment suddenly begins to seem not like a temporary phase, but a protracted life on someone else’s rules. Own housing attracts not with luxury, but with the promise of finally stopping being a guest.\n\nBut for Aidar, a mortgage sounds like a long phrase with no room for error. It requires a future that must be believed in advance: that work will remain, health will endure, the market will not redraw everything again.\n\nNow he can go into debt, continue saving, or consciously choose renting as more free, albeit not so “adult” in the eyes of the family.",
    "evt_aidar_2024_mortgage_offer_opt_take_mortgage" to "Enter into a mortgage and stop living temporarily",
    "evt_aidar_2024_mortgage_offer_opt_skip_mortgage" to "Continue saving and not tie yourself to debt",
    "evt_aidar_2024_startup_aftershock_msg" to "The delayed consequence comes not with a letter, but with fatigue and numbers. The startup takes more attention than it promised, the partnership turns out to be less smooth than it seemed at the beginning, and romance quickly gives way to accounting and responsibility.\n\nAidar sees how decisions have a tail. What looked like inspiration three months ago now requires a re-decision: he is still building his future or is simply keeping a fragile structure from falling.\n\nYou can reduce participation and save the resource, or you can invest again, because it’s scary to admit: sometimes a good start doesn’t have to become a big story.",
    "evt_aidar_2024_startup_aftershock_opt_aftershock_scale" to "Stay in the game and pay for the chance with more attention",
    "evt_aidar_2024_startup_aftershock_opt_aftershock_exit" to "Carefully move away and save the base.",
    "evt_aidar_2024_normal_life_msg" to "A month passed without any major changes. Work, phone calls, travel, short dinners, bank notifications, other people's successes in the feed and your own life, which still needs to be built from ordinary days.\n\nIt is in such months that the future is decided. Not in moments of beautiful risk, but in repetitions: what Aidar does with extra money, how he deals with his fatigue, what he says “yes” to without witnesses.\n\nThis time he has the opportunity to strengthen his footing, invest in knowledge, or try to speed up again.",
    "evt_aidar_2024_normal_life_opt_invest_etf" to "Invest some of your peace of mind",
    "evt_aidar_2024_normal_life_opt_online_course" to "Buy your next professional shoulder",
    "evt_aidar_2024_normal_life_opt_save_cash" to "Don't prove anything to the world and just increase your cushion",
    "evt_aidar_2024_normal_life_opt_network_it" to "Go to people and look for the next door",
    "evt_aidar_2024_ending_startup_king_msg" to "At some point, Aidar stopped being the guy trying to catch up with the market. Now the market itself is looking for a meeting with him. The company has grown, people inside talk about the product as something reliable, and not a daring attempt.\n\nHe often recalls how afraid he was of his first big expense and his first real risk. Not because he misses poverty, but because he now understands: wealth does not come from luck, but from the ability to withstand your decisions longer than someone else’s delight can withstand.\n\nThe era of {eraLabel} is a thing of the past. Capital {capital}. Aidar now has not just money, but a scale in which he can choose who and what to build next.",
    "evt_aidar_2024_ending_senior_dev_msg" to "Aidar did not become the hero of loud headlines. But he became a person you can rely on. He has a name in his career, there is a rhythm in his life, and in his head there is finally less chaos than there was before.\n\nHe no longer confuses stability with weakness. For him, this is not a refusal to grow, but a form of self-respect: to live in such a way that there is enough strength not only for work, but also for life around it.\n\nCapital {capital}, income {income}. Not a fairy tale, but honestly built soil under your feet.",
    "evt_aidar_2024_ending_freedom_msg" to "Freedom came to Aidar not as a loud event, but as one quiet thought in the morning: today you can work not out of fear. You can choose projects, pace, people. You can refuse.\n\nThis feeling turned out to be more valuable than all the fantasies about quick victories. Because for the first time in many years, his decisions are not dictated by urgency, other people's expectations, or the need to urgently prove his own worth.\n\nCapital {capital}. Now he has not only income, but also space for his own life.",
    "evt_aidar_2024_ending_broke_msg" to "There comes a time when there is no longer any point in pretending that everything is under control. There is almost no money, decisions have accumulated a heavy tail, and shame speaks louder than any calculations.\n\nAidar is experiencing not only financial loss. He experiences the collapse of his own beautiful version of himself. And it hurts more. But it is at this point that he first separates dignity from success.\n\nCapital is almost empty. The story ended hard, but not uselessly: now he knows the value of those decisions that previously seemed romantic.",
    "evt_aidar_2024_ending_paycheck_msg" to "Life didn't collapse. And this has its own silence. There is work, money comes, obligations are closed. But nothing really moves.\n\nAidar looks at himself without cruelty. He didn’t lose loudly, but he also didn’t take himself to a place where there are more elections. Sometimes the worst trap looks like this: like normality without movement.\n\nIncome comes, capital hardly grows. It's not the end, but it's definitely not a chapter he wants to reread.",
    "evt_aidar_2024_debt_crisis_msg" to "The bank sends a message without emotion, but the body responds to it instantly: cold in the stomach, dry mouth, irritation at everything around. Debt ceased to be a number in the application and became the main character of the month.\n\nAidar realizes that he was pulling too many things at once. At some point, ambition and fatigue begin to work against him on the same team.\n\nThere is little money, the debt is {debt}, the account is {capital}. Now we need not to dream, but to save maneuverability.",
    "evt_aidar_2024_debt_crisis_opt_sell_investments" to "Cut off a beautiful future and close an urgent hole",
    "evt_aidar_2024_debt_crisis_opt_debt_restructure" to "Go to the bank and ask for restructuring without pride",
    "evt_aidar_2024_burnout_warning_msg" to "He is still able to work, but he is almost unable to enjoy what he worked so hard for. This is a warning sign: if you ignore it for too long, any career victory will begin to feel like a punishment.\n\nVacations now seem like a luxury. But perhaps it's the luxury of a pause that's keeping him from falling more expensively.",
    "evt_aidar_2024_burnout_warning_opt_take_vacation" to "Take a break and get your head back",
    "evt_aidar_2024_burnout_warning_opt_push_through" to "Tell yourself again “just a little more”",
    "evt_aidar_2024_investment_unlock_msg" to "At this moment, Aidar for the first time feels not excitement, but quiet confidence. He no longer looks for magic in money. He is looking for discipline that will allow time to do the work for him.\n\nYou can open a new level in your relationship with finances or put it off and stay a little longer in observer mode.",
    "evt_aidar_2024_investment_unlock_opt_open_iis" to "Open an account and put knowledge into action",
    "evt_aidar_2024_investment_unlock_opt_skip_iis" to "Leave this door for later",
    "evt_aidar_2024_ending_broke_trigger_msg" to "It's not about the next step anymore. Further about the recognition that the old structure has collapsed.",
    "evt_aidar_2024_ending_broke_trigger_opt_accept_broke" to "Admit failure and stop",
    "evt_aidar_2024_ending_freedom_trigger_msg" to "One day the numbers add up in such a way that for the first time fear does not have time to wake up before confidence.",
    "evt_aidar_2024_ending_freedom_trigger_opt_claim_freedom" to "Recognize that freedom has already been pieced together",
    "evt_aidar_2024_ending_stability_trigger_msg" to "Life stopped shaking with every decision. It may be quieter than a dream, but sometimes silence is the reward.",
    "evt_aidar_2024_ending_stability_trigger_opt_claim_stability" to "Settle on honestly built sustainability",
    "evt_aidar_2024_ending_wealth_trigger_msg" to "The startup story ceased to be an attempt and became a new financial reality.",
    "evt_aidar_2024_ending_wealth_trigger_opt_claim_wealth" to "Take your big ending",
    "evt_aidar_2024_ending_paycheck_trigger_msg" to "Months go by, and the room for maneuver has not increased.",
    "evt_aidar_2024_ending_paycheck_trigger_opt_accept_paycheck" to "Recognize living paycheck to paycheck",
    "evt_dana_2005_intro_msg" to "2005 Dana walks home after school through the damp spring yard and counts not her steps, but the coming months. The husband works with his hands, she holds other people's notebooks in her hands, and their own life is still fit into a rented apartment with thin walls.\n\nShe is thirty-two, and she too often hears the phrase “we need to be patient a little longer.” Patience has become almost a family profession. But stubborn mathematics lives inside Dana: if every month everything is planned down to the last penny, then one day the output can be calculated.\n\nThe account is {capital}. Income {income}. There is only enough money for a neat life without the right to surprise. A colleague talks about private students, and the neighbor again whispers that “she won’t buy her own home.”",
    "evt_dana_2005_intro_opt_start_tutoring" to "Try tutoring and steal another chance for your family",
    "evt_dana_2005_intro_opt_explore_mortgage" to "First, understand what the path to your apartment generally looks like",
    "evt_dana_2005_tutoring_platform_msg" to "The first student comes on a recommendation, the second brings two cousins, the third already pays without bargaining. Tutoring does not look like a big change, but it is precisely such quiet increases that sometimes change the fate of a family more than the loud promises of the state.\n\nDana already feels guilty in advance. Every evening lesson is both a relief and lost time with her daughter. The money comes right, but not free.\n\nYou can strengthen this direction, leave it as a small support, or curtail it until life begins to consist only of other people’s expectations.",
    "evt_dana_2005_tutoring_platform_opt_join_platform" to "Seriously integrate tutoring into your life",
    "evt_dana_2005_tutoring_platform_opt_skip_platform" to "Leave your strength at home and don’t split yourself up",
    "evt_dana_2005_tutoring_growth_msg" to "A few months later, Dana already had a small evening school in her kitchen. Notebooks lie in piles, the tea gets cold, and other people’s children regularly appear at the table, to whom she gives not only knowledge, but also the much-needed feeling that the adult nearby is collected.\n\nOne of the parents offers the unexpected: rent a small office and gather your own group. It's more money and more risk. For Dana, this is also the first chance in her life not just to earn extra money, but to build something of her own, without ceasing to be herself.\n\nThe question is not whether she is capable. The question is whether the family is ready to live with this new load.",
    "evt_dana_2005_tutoring_growth_opt_launch_school" to "Open a small study group and take a chance on growth",
    "evt_dana_2005_tutoring_growth_opt_stay_quiet" to "Keep everything private and safe",
    "evt_dana_2005_mortgage_decision_msg" to "The conversation about the apartment comes up again in the evening in the kitchen. Not like a dream, but like almost physical fatigue from someone else’s walls, someone else’s rules, a landlady who can raise the rent just when the child needs a new jacket.\n\nDana counts the numbers and understands: in 2005, for them, their own housing is still more like a long route than a single decision. But right now you can choose a direction: save more aggressively, take a risk with a loan, or admit that liquidity is more important to the family.\n\nA mistake here will cost more than just money. It will hit the sense of security that Dana builds for her loved ones almost single-handedly.",
    "evt_dana_2005_mortgage_decision_opt_take_mortgage" to "Take out a loan earlier than it is convenient for you",
    "evt_dana_2005_mortgage_decision_opt_save_more" to "Save more and don’t let the bank get too close",
    "evt_dana_2005_mortgage_decision_opt_rent_forever" to "For now, stay rented and maintain flexibility",
    "evt_dana_2015_intro_msg" to "2015 In the news feed they are arguing about the tenge exchange rate, and at Dana’s house they are arguing about whether to take out a mortgage before prices run even further. She still teaches children mathematics, only now the world around them has become a task with constantly changing conditions.\n\nDana is used to living cautiously, but caution is beginning to wear out. When the currency twitches, prices creep up, and the child has school ahead of him, simple accuracy no longer seems to be a sufficient strategy.\n\nShe has {capital} savings, {income} income and the habit of holding her family in her hands even when her hands themselves are shaking. She has two options before her: try to turn her knowledge into additional income or lean even harder into the idea of ​​her own apartment.",
    "evt_dana_2015_intro_opt_start_tutoring" to "Make tutoring a real second income",
    "evt_dana_2015_intro_opt_explore_mortgage" to "Deal with your mortgage before reality changes again",
    "evt_dana_2015_tutoring_platform_msg" to "Online platforms promise a new market for teachers. Dana finds this both convenient and slightly humiliating: now she needs to sell not only knowledge, but also herself as a service, answer quickly, write beautifully, keep a schedule without the right to weakness.\n\nAnd yet there is hope in this. For the first time, additional income may not depend on the whim of the school principal. For the first time, her professionalism is able to bring money directly to her.\n\nIt remains to be decided whether she wants to open this door for real or leave it ajar.",
    "evt_dana_2015_tutoring_platform_opt_join_platform" to "Get serious and build yourself a second support",
    "evt_dana_2015_tutoring_platform_opt_skip_platform" to "Don't ruin the evening and save the family's strength",
    "evt_dana_2015_tutoring_growth_msg" to "The platform worked better than expected. Students come consistently, parents thank them, and Dana for the first time sees how knowledge turns not just into respect, but into real money that can be spent on the future.\n\nA new fork appears. One parent suggests gathering a mini-group online and doing a course. This is almost a small matter. For Dana, accustomed to being cautious, such a step sounds bold and almost wrong.\n\nBut sometimes your own courage begins precisely with the fact that you stop considering yourself a person just for stability.",
    "evt_dana_2015_tutoring_growth_opt_launch_school" to "Build your first online group and take the risk of growth",
    "evt_dana_2015_tutoring_growth_opt_stay_quiet" to "Leave everything as a quiet side hustle",
    "evt_dana_2015_mortgage_decision_msg" to "The bank smiles in its advertising brochures, as if a mortgage is just an adult form of dream. Dana sees something else: many years of payments, dependence on one or two incomes and fear of any crisis that may not come as scheduled.\n\nAt the same time, a rented apartment increasingly feels like a temporary life. The child needs stability. She herself wants to finally stop explaining to her daughter why she can’t draw on this wallpaper, because it’s not theirs.\n\nThe decision will have to be made not with the heart and not only with logic. You will have to accept it with your whole body, which will then live with or without this debt.",
    "evt_dana_2015_mortgage_decision_opt_take_mortgage" to "Take out a mortgage and settle your family in your home",
    "evt_dana_2015_mortgage_decision_opt_save_more" to "For now, save up and keep room for maneuver",
    "evt_dana_2015_mortgage_decision_opt_rent_forever" to "Capture and direct the difference towards a more flexible future",
    "evt_dana_2024_intro_msg" to "2024 Dana has long been not just a teacher, but a person whom parents of students advise each other in a whisper: “if you want your child not to be afraid of mathematics, go to her.” But reputation does not always translate into an easy life.\n\nSchool during the day, online classes in the evening, anxiety at night that good people in education are being asked to work their butts off. She loves her job, but increasingly asks herself the question: is it possible to maintain the meaning of work and at the same time stop constantly living on the edge.\n\nShe has {capital}, income {income}, a family that rests on her dedication, and a chance to turn teaching into an edtech direction. But any growth has a price: time, nerves, attention to loved ones.",
    "evt_dana_2024_intro_opt_start_tutoring" to "Transfer talent to a modern online format",
    "evt_dana_2024_intro_opt_explore_mortgage" to "First, bring to mind the issue of home and basic support",
    "evt_dana_2024_tutoring_platform_msg" to "The platform asks you to make a welcome video, create a profile, respond quickly and speak about yourself confidently. For some this is a small thing, but for Dana it’s almost a new profession. Now it’s not enough to be a good teacher, you also need to be able to not be ashamed of your value.\n\nThe first students come quickly, and with them comes a new idea: if you build a system, you can stop selling only your evenings and start selling the method. It already looks like a small business.\n\nShe can take a step towards edtech, or she can leave everything as an additional, but manageable income.",
    "evt_dana_2024_tutoring_platform_opt_join_platform" to "Launch a serious online direction",
    "evt_dana_2024_tutoring_platform_opt_skip_platform" to "Leave teaching in a warm, intimate format",
    "evt_dana_2024_tutoring_growth_msg" to "Online groups are growing faster than Dana can get used to her new role. People buy her lessons not only for their knowledge, but also for the peace of mind that she knows how to create. This is a rare talent and the market has suddenly taken notice.\n\nOne producer I know suggests putting together a full-fledged course, hiring an assistant and stopping making income only for her personal time. Dana sees both an opportunity and a threat in this: will the main thing be washed away if it all becomes too big.\n\nThe choice is no longer between money and meaning, but between different ways to maintain meaning without dooming yourself to chronic burnout.",
    "evt_dana_2024_tutoring_growth_opt_launch_school" to "Assemble a mini-team and turn experience into a system",
    "evt_dana_2024_tutoring_growth_opt_stay_quiet" to "Leave everything to personal quality and don’t grow through force",
    "evt_dana_2024_mortgage_decision_msg" to "A house in 2024 for Dana does not mean status, but the right to finally live without the internal “if anything happens, we will be asked to move out.” After pandemics, price hikes and a general feeling of instability, this right has become almost a basic dream.\n\nBut she is already old enough not to confuse a dream with an obligation. A mortgage can give the walls names, but at the same time take away the flexibility that the family still uses as insurance against the unexpected.\n\nAgain, she faces the same adult mathematics: how much can she afford without the house becoming a new form of anxiety.",
    "evt_dana_2024_mortgage_decision_opt_take_mortgage" to "Take out a mortgage and move your family into your own space",
    "evt_dana_2024_mortgage_decision_opt_save_more" to "Wait a little longer and buy yourself more air",
    "evt_dana_2024_mortgage_decision_opt_rent_forever" to "Leave the lease and bet on liquidity and investment",
    "evt_dana_2024_child_education_msg" to "Dana knows well that not only school and clubs are important for a child. But she also knows the value of the environment. Sometimes she feels guilty just from the mere fact that she has to choose between the good and the possible.\n\nThe family budget must be protected without turning the child into an eternal justification for any expense. This is a thin and painful line.",
    "evt_dana_2024_child_education_opt_private_school" to "Pay more for a strong environment and peace of mind",
    "evt_dana_2024_child_education_opt_state_tutor" to "Keep public school, but add individual support",
    "evt_dana_2024_child_education_opt_state_school" to "Keep your base under control and not blow your budget",
    "evt_dana_2024_husband_layoff_msg" to "In the evening, the husband sits down opposite and is silent for a long time before saying the main thing: the job has been cut. It is phrases like these that change the temperature in the house more than any cold weather.\n\nFor Dana, this means more than just minus one income. This means that her own composure again becomes the central supporting structure of the family, and this almost physically hurts her shoulders.\n\nYou can sharply tighten your belt, live on reserve, or turn her work into an even more difficult, but profitable burden.",
    "evt_dana_2024_husband_layoff_opt_cut_expenses" to "Cut expenses before panic does it for them",
    "evt_dana_2024_husband_layoff_opt_use_savings" to "Let the family breathe through savings",
    "evt_dana_2024_husband_layoff_opt_more_tutoring" to "Take on even more students",
    "evt_dana_2024_normal_life_msg" to "Outwardly, the month passes calmly: lessons, notebooks, groceries, family conversations, rare quiet evenings. But it is precisely in such months that Dana builds her future, almost unnoticed by those around her.\n\nHer life has long consisted of decisions that do not look heroic. And yet they are the ones who determine whether the family will live in constant anxiety or gradually gain stability.\n\nThis time, free money can be used for savings, knowledge, conservative investments, or simply rebuilding your family.",
    "evt_dana_2024_normal_life_opt_family_savings" to "Put the extra in the family pillow",
    "evt_dana_2024_normal_life_opt_read_finance" to "Understand money more deeply to be less afraid of it",
    "evt_dana_2024_normal_life_opt_invest_conservative" to "Choose a cautious tool instead of empty waiting",
    "evt_dana_2024_normal_life_opt_family_trip" to "Spend on intimacy, not just sustainability",
    "evt_dana_2024_ending_own_school_msg" to "Dana has built not just a profitable project, but a space where children cease to be afraid of mathematics, and adults finally see in her profession not a “calling in spite of,” but real capital.\n\nFor a long time she was afraid that growth would take away her meaning. But it turned out to be the opposite: when there was less chaos, there was more energy for real teaching. Now her work does not burn her out, but expands her.\n\nThe era of {eraLabel} is behind us. Capital {capital}. And most importantly, the family no longer has the feeling that sustainability has to be literally scratched out every month.",
    "evt_dana_2024_ending_stable_family_msg" to "Dana did not become a person from business magazines. She became a person who managed to make the house a place of peace, rather than constant anxiety. Sometimes this is the rarest form of victory.\n\nThere is still a lot to do in her life, but there is less fear. The child grows up in predictability, relationships are no longer held together by constant economic panic, and money has finally stopped dictating the tone of every conversation.\n\nCapital {capital}. The sustainability turned out not to be luxurious, but honest. And that's why it's so expensive.",
    "evt_dana_2024_ending_freedom_msg" to "One day Dana catches herself with a simple thought: now she can work because she loves, and not because she’s afraid to stop. This is a new, almost unusual state.\n\nShe still teaches, but does it without internal trembling for each subsequent month. Income from the system and capital covers basic expenses, which means you no longer need to tear yourself apart for the sake of the very fact of sustainability.\n\nCapital {capital}. Freedom for her does not look like a luxury, but like the restored right to one’s own rhythm.",
    "evt_dana_2024_ending_debt_trap_msg" to "Life did not fall apart, but turned into a chain of payments. Mortgage, repairs, school, household expenses. Each new month begins a little guilty.\n\nDana is still going strong. But all her strength is spent on maintaining the structure, in which there is almost no room left for either joy or calm growth.\n\nDebt {debt}. The family is afloat, but the water is always too close.",
    "evt_dana_2024_ending_bankruptcy_msg" to "The hardest thing here isn’t even the numbers. The hardest thing is the feeling that all the years of carefulness still did not protect them from falling. The house ceases to be a home again, and the future has to be assembled almost from scratch.\n\nDana experiences this failure not as the end of her dignity, but as a difficult but honest mark: caution without reserve and without strategy is also vulnerable. And she will never forget this lesson.\n\nCapital is depleted. But the experience remained. This means the story is not completely over yet.",
    "evt_dana_2024_debt_crisis_msg" to "The bank sends the notice in dry, official language, but Dana reads it with her whole body. She knows all too well how quickly one delay turns into months of anxiety and humiliating conversations.\n\nShe doesn't need heroism now. She needs cold precision to save her family from a cascade of consequences.\n\nDebt {debt}, capital {capital}. It's time to choose what exactly to pay for survival: investments, pride or even greater internal tension.",
    "evt_dana_2024_debt_crisis_opt_sell_investments" to "Sell ​​what you have accumulated and close the urgent hole",
    "evt_dana_2024_debt_crisis_opt_ask_parents" to "Ask for help and swallow the awkwardness",
    "evt_dana_2024_burnout_warning_msg" to "Her problem isn't that she doesn't like her job much. On the contrary: she pulled out everything for too long on one sense of duty. Any calling breaks down one day if it is used as free fuel.\n\nYou need to either give yourself a break, or admit that Dana again chooses not herself.",
    "evt_dana_2024_burnout_warning_opt_take_break" to "Take a step back and get your breath back",
    "evt_dana_2024_burnout_warning_opt_reduce_tutoring" to "Reduce the load and not die from usefulness",
    "evt_dana_2024_investment_unlock_msg" to "For Dana, this is an important internal turn. She stops perceiving finances as the territory of other people's confident people and for the first time feels that she can make decisions not out of fear, but out of understanding.\n\nThere is a chance to take the next step carefully, but not passively.",
    "evt_dana_2024_investment_unlock_opt_buy_bonds" to "Choose a predictable tool and commit to discipline",
    "evt_dana_2024_investment_unlock_opt_skip_bonds" to "For now, leave the money closer to your hand",
    "evt_dana_2024_ending_wealth_trigger_msg" to "The system assembled by Denmark ceased to depend only on its wear and tear and turned into real capital.",
    "evt_dana_2024_ending_wealth_trigger_opt_claim_wealth" to "Recognize the big victory",
    "evt_dana_2024_ending_freedom_trigger_msg" to "Anxiety no longer rules every family decision.",
    "evt_dana_2024_ending_freedom_trigger_opt_claim_freedom" to "Enter the chapter of financial freedom",
    "evt_dana_2024_ending_stability_trigger_msg" to "Finally, the family system does not work on a miracle, but on sustainability.",
    "evt_dana_2024_ending_stability_trigger_opt_claim_stability" to "Secure a calm ending",
    "evt_dana_2024_ending_bankruptcy_trigger_msg" to "What follows is no longer about planning, but about recognizing a hard fall.",
    "evt_dana_2024_ending_bankruptcy_trigger_opt_claim_bankruptcy" to "Stop and acknowledge the collapse",
    "evt_dana_2024_ending_paycheck_trigger_msg" to "The months have become similar to each other and belong almost entirely to obligations.",
    "evt_dana_2024_ending_paycheck_trigger_opt_claim_debt_trap" to "Capturing life in a debt trap",
    "evt_erbolat_2015_intro_msg" to "2015 Erbolat stands in the emptying hall of the second store and for the first time notices that the music in the shopping center sounds too cheerful for his reality. The revenue is still holding, but the margin has already become thin, like someone else’s patience.\n\nHe used to consider himself a man of action. Such people do not complain, do not show fear and always find the next move. But every entrepreneur has a moment when the word “moving” begins to hide simple fatigue from constant responsibility.\n\nHe has debt {debt}, capital {capital}, family and business, which can still pull them up, or can drag them down entirely. Gulnara speaks cautiously about reducing risks. Erbolat himself is still drawn to the idea of ​​a big move.",
    "evt_erbolat_2015_intro_opt_close_second_store" to "Scale down before the market forces you to do so",
    "evt_erbolat_2015_intro_opt_fight_competition" to "Go on the attack and squeeze growth out of the old model",
    "evt_erbolat_2015_intro_opt_wait_and_see" to "Observe a little more and don’t jump too quickly",
    "evt_erbolat_2015_franchise_offer_msg" to "A representative of a large chain speaks very confidently. A franchise sounds like someone else’s order that you can simply buy: brand, standards, advertising, logistics, as if with money comes less anxiety.\n\nFor Erbolat this is a special kind of temptation. He's tired of being the person who comes up with everything himself. Being able to rely on a ready-made system seems almost like a luxury. But this luxury is sold on credit and with a very long tail of obligations.\n\nIf he comes in, the debt will increase. If he refuses, he will have to admit it himself: saving the business still lies with his own decisions.",
    "evt_erbolat_2015_franchise_offer_opt_take_franchise" to "Buy a system and hope that scale will save you",
    "evt_erbolat_2015_franchise_offer_opt_skip_franchise" to "Refuse and keep debt within reality",
    "evt_erbolat_2015_franchise_offer_opt_negotiate_franchise" to "Bargain and not take on the entire proposed scale",
    "evt_erbolat_2015_franchise_result_msg" to "Six months later, Erbolat looks at the numbers and understands: an increase in turnover in itself is not a victory. The revenue became more beautiful, but along with it, expenses also increased, and for some reason there was no increase in freedom.\n\nThis is a painful discovery for a man who has been conditioned to believe that scale almost automatically justifies risk. Now it’s clear: you can become bigger and at the same time become more vulnerable.\n\nThere is a fork in front of him again. Continue pressing and build almost an empire, or admit that the main task now is not expansion, but saving the quality of life and maneuverability.",
    "evt_erbolat_2015_franchise_result_opt_third_store" to "Go ahead and buy growth on debt",
    "evt_erbolat_2015_franchise_result_opt_master_franchise" to "Bet on a very big game",
    "evt_erbolat_2015_franchise_result_opt_hold_position" to "Stop and learn to hold on first",
    "evt_erbolat_2015_ecommerce_pivot_msg" to "Gulnara shows the phone screen as a medical image of the future: sales are moving online. While Erbolat was arguing with rent and suppliers, the market had already learned to buy differently.\n\nFor him, this is almost a blow to his pride. He built himself as an offline entrepreneur, a man of the point, a shop window, and a face-to-face conversation with a client. The transition to digital feels not just like a new channel, but as an acknowledgment that the old way is no longer the center.\n\nBut this is where salvation may lie: a quick marketplace, your own website, or an attempt to do everything at once and work hard again.",
    "evt_erbolat_2015_ecommerce_pivot_opt_kaspi_marketplace" to "Go where there is already traffic and money",
    "evt_erbolat_2015_ecommerce_pivot_opt_own_website" to "Build independence, even if it's slower",
    "evt_erbolat_2015_ecommerce_pivot_opt_both_channels" to "Capture everything at once and live in overload mode",
    "evt_erbolat_2024_intro_msg" to "2024 Erbolat no longer has just shops, but the fatigue of a man who has held the business for too long by his personal will. Now problems come not only from offline: marketplaces are putting pressure on margins, suppliers demand prepayment, the tax office wants transparency, and the family wants to see a living person at home, and not a director who is always on.\n\nHe still knows how to collect money from chaos, but he is increasingly less able to collect himself. In his world, success has long ceased to be a beautiful word and has become synonymous with round-the-clock availability.\n\nCapital {capital}, income {income}, debt {debt}. The business can still be scaled up, it can be improved, it can be reassembled into a calmer and more technologically advanced system. But we can’t pretend that nothing is changing.",
    "evt_erbolat_2024_intro_opt_close_second_store" to "Reduce offline and return oxygen to business",
    "evt_erbolat_2024_intro_opt_fight_competition" to "Fight for market share and not give the stage to marketplaces",
    "evt_erbolat_2024_intro_opt_wait_and_see" to "Leave everything as is for another quarter",
    "evt_erbolat_2024_franchise_offer_msg" to "This time the offer sounds more modern: not just a franchise, but a connection to a federal digital system with CRM, advertising, analytics and a recognizable brand. Everything that Erbolat himself always lacked either time or discipline for.\n\nIt's not just greed that draws him to this deal. He is drawn by the hope that someone will finally bring order to his constantly humming car. But the price of order is still written in debt and concessions in control.\n\nYou need to decide whether to buy someone else's system if it can simultaneously save the business and make it less of your own.",
    "evt_erbolat_2024_franchise_offer_opt_take_franchise" to "Go deep and buy scale along with control",
    "evt_erbolat_2024_franchise_offer_opt_skip_franchise" to "Don't sell peace of mind for a beautiful shell",
    "evt_erbolat_2024_franchise_offer_opt_negotiate_franchise" to "Enter partially and bargain for less dependence",
    "evt_erbolat_2024_franchise_result_msg" to "Business is becoming more technologically advanced, but also colder. The numbers look better, the processes are more transparent, but Erbolat suddenly feels that every next decision now requires coordination not only with the market, but also with someone else’s model.\n\nThis is a useful but unpleasant lesson. You can stop drowning in chaos and still lose the feeling that the company belongs to you not only legally, but also internally.\n\nNext you need to choose: put pressure on scale again or make the business sustainable without turning yourself into an operator of someone else’s template.",
    "evt_erbolat_2024_franchise_result_opt_third_store" to "Open another point and take the growth by number",
    "evt_erbolat_2024_franchise_result_opt_master_franchise" to "Go for a really big game",
    "evt_erbolat_2024_franchise_result_opt_hold_position" to "Fix the scale and improve the quality of life",
    "evt_erbolat_2024_ecommerce_pivot_msg" to "In 2024, the digital revolution no longer looks like an experiment. It looks like a sanitary measure. If Erbolat does not rebuild the business, the market itself will rebuild it without demand.\n\nGulnara speaks harshly: we need marketplaces, analytics, transparent accounting, fast logistics and normal tax discipline. For Erbolat, this sounds like an admission that the charisma of an entrepreneur no longer replaces the system.\n\nHe can make a quick leap through ready-made platforms, build his own channel, or again choose overload as the universal language of salvation.",
    "evt_erbolat_2024_ecommerce_pivot_opt_kaspi_marketplace" to "Make friends with the marketplace and stop fighting with the real thing",
    "evt_erbolat_2024_ecommerce_pivot_opt_own_website" to "Make your own channel and keep more control",
    "evt_erbolat_2024_ecommerce_pivot_opt_both_channels" to "Take on everything at once again",
    "evt_erbolat_common_supplier_scam_msg" to "The new supplier offers too good conditions. This is precisely what is alarming. Over the years of business, Erbolat has developed intuition, but he also knows its weakness: when there is not enough money, suspicions begin to seem like a luxury.\n\nThe contract looks decent, the manager responds quickly, the price is almost indecently favorable. Everything in this deal seems to be specially configured so that the entrepreneur is tired of doubting.\n\nYou can risk your working capital, spend money on verification, or refuse and continue to live with the thought that you may have missed your chance.",
    "evt_erbolat_common_supplier_scam_opt_pay_supplier" to "Transfer money and hope that fortune still favors the brave",
    "evt_erbolat_common_supplier_scam_opt_check_supplier" to "Pay for verification and buy yourself clarity",
    "evt_erbolat_common_supplier_scam_opt_skip_supplier" to "Don't go into too sweet a story",
    "evt_erbolat_common_supplier_result_msg" to "The cargo doesn't arrive. The phone is turned off. The money has gone to a place where it no longer has a name. For an entrepreneur, this is not just a loss of money, but humiliation: you were caught in your own fatigue and greed for relief.\n\nErbolat is angry primarily with himself. Not for taking a risk, but for taking a risk without structure. In this episode, not only money is destroyed, but also the usual sense of control over the situation.\n\nNow he needs to either harshly accept the lesson and rebuild, or spend more energy trying to return what may have already disappeared.",
    "evt_erbolat_common_supplier_result_opt_cut_losses" to "Digest the loss and move on to repair the business",
    "evt_erbolat_common_supplier_result_opt_sue_supplier" to "Litigate, even if the chances are low",
    "evt_erbolat_common_supplier_safe_msg" to "The lawyer looks at the papers for just a few minutes and immediately says what Erbolat already seemed to know inside: this is a dummy. This time it was not scent or luck that saved him, but discipline.\n\nThis is almost a new experience for him. Checking seems expensive only until you consider the cost of making a mistake. After that, it looks like the cheapest investment of the month.\n\nNow you can go through trusted people or again try to negotiate the market alone.",
    "evt_erbolat_common_supplier_safe_opt_find_reliable" to "Pay for reliability and strengthen the operating system",
    "evt_erbolat_common_supplier_safe_opt_search_yourself" to "Search on your own, but no longer blindly",
    "evt_erbolat_common_normal_life_msg" to "Another operating month. Salaries, rent, suppliers, returns, tax issues, family conversations, fatigue, which has almost become the background. Business lives not only by big decisions, but also by an endless series of small management actions.\n\nErbolat realized long ago: if he does not give money direction, it will find the most noisy and ineffective way out for itself.\n\nFree resources can be used to reduce debt, increase traffic, goods, or your own managerial head.",
    "evt_erbolat_common_normal_life_opt_pay_debt" to "Pay off some debt and buy yourself a little more sleep.",
    "evt_erbolat_common_normal_life_opt_marketing" to "Buy the market's attention rather than wait for its favor",
    "evt_erbolat_common_normal_life_opt_inventory" to "Invest in assortment and hope for the season",
    "evt_erbolat_common_normal_life_opt_finance_course" to "Learn to manage more maturely than before",
    "evt_erbolat_common_ending_empire_msg" to "Erbolat managed to go from a person who extinguished operational fires with his nervous system to the owner of a real system. The business stopped being based on his personal panic and began to work as a structure.\n\nHe is still an entrepreneur, but no longer a person who must personally be in all places at once. This is the main wealth that comes with numbers: taking back your own life, not just multiplying your assets.\n\nThe era of {eraLabel} is behind us. Capital {capital}. Now the scale does not devour him, but obeys him.",
    "evt_erbolat_common_ending_pivot_success_msg" to "Erbolat’s most mature victory was not in opening as many points as possible, but in letting go of his old identity in time. He transferred the business to a digital model and stopped confusing volume with quality of life.\n\nIncome has become more stable, the debt stranglehold has eased, the family again sees people at home, and not just an overexcited control center.\n\nCapital {capital}. Freedom came to him in the form of clarity and controllability.",
    "evt_erbolat_common_ending_stable_business_msg" to "Erbolat didn’t take the market by storm, but he did put together a much rarer thing for his family: a business that doesn’t fall apart with every bad month. Sometimes this is what mature entrepreneurship is all about.\n\nHe no longer lives in constant anxiety mode. The company is working, the debt is under control, the house has ceased to be a branch of the office.\n\nCapital {capital}. This is not a legend about a meteoric rise, but a story about honestly won stability.",
    "evt_erbolat_common_ending_bankruptcy_msg" to "The worst thing about bankruptcy for Erbolat is not the loss of stores. The worst thing is to admit that all this time he measured himself only by his ability to hold and drag. When business goes down, that old, tough version of masculinity goes down with it.\n\nBut it is in the ruins that he has a chance to understand himself not as a collection of assets, but as a person who can still build a new life without previous illusions.\n\nCapital is depleted, debt crushes the structure. The story ended painfully, but whether it is final or not depends no longer on the market.",
    "evt_erbolat_common_ending_paycheck_msg" to "The business is still alive, but it lives like a person after a serious illness: it moves, breathes, but there is no strength for a new breakthrough. It takes me every month just to not fall.\n\nErbolat is still an entrepreneur on paper, but internally he has long been working on obligations rather than on dreams. This state does not have the drama of a big collapse, but there is the viscous fatigue of daily survival.\n\nDebt {debt}, capital {capital}. Not a disaster, but not the life for which it all began.",
    "evt_erbolat_common_debt_crisis_msg" to "The bank stops talking respectfully. When money becomes scarce, any partner very quickly remembers who is actually weaker in negotiations.\n\nErbolat hates this moment, because a confident voice and entrepreneurial temperament no longer work here. Only numbers work, and numbers are more stubborn than anything.\n\nDebt {debt}, capital {capital}. You have to choose what exactly to cut: scale, share, pride or future income.",
    "evt_erbolat_common_debt_crisis_opt_sell_store" to "Sell ​​part of the business to save the rest",
    "evt_erbolat_common_debt_crisis_opt_bank_restructure" to "Go to restructuring and buy yourself time",
    "evt_erbolat_common_debt_crisis_opt_find_investor" to "Let the investor in and share control",
    "evt_erbolat_common_burnout_warning_msg" to "For Erbolat, rest for a long time seemed like a weakness. Now the doctor, wife and own body are saying the same thing: if you don’t stop, the business will get an owner who is still in place, but no longer makes clear decisions.\n\nIt's time to recognize that delegation and pausing are also forms of power.",
    "evt_erbolat_common_burnout_warning_opt_family_vacation" to "Break yourself out of anxiety mode for at least two weeks",
    "evt_erbolat_common_burnout_warning_opt_delegate" to "Hire a manager and buy your own air",
    "evt_erbolat_common_investment_unlock_msg" to "It's a frustrating but important part of growing a business: recognizing that entrepreneurial intuition doesn't have to solve everything alone. Tools, processes and financial discipline do not kill acumen, but protect it from chaos.\n\nErbolat can use a new tool now or continue to manage as he was used to before.",
    "evt_erbolat_common_investment_unlock_opt_use_factoring" to "Connect the tool and return agility to your business",
    "evt_erbolat_common_investment_unlock_opt_skip_factoring" to "Remain in the old style of management",
    "evt_erbolat_common_ending_bankruptcy_trigger_msg" to "All ways to delay the blow have ended.",
    "evt_erbolat_common_ending_bankruptcy_trigger_opt_claim_bankruptcy" to "Admit bankruptcy",
    "evt_erbolat_common_ending_wealth_trigger_msg" to "The business has grown so much that it no longer feeds solely on the owner’s nervous system.",
    "evt_erbolat_common_ending_wealth_trigger_opt_claim_empire" to "Take the big ending",
    "evt_erbolat_common_ending_freedom_trigger_msg" to "Business restructuring finally began to work for Erbolat, and not just require more and more strength from him.",
    "evt_erbolat_common_ending_freedom_trigger_opt_claim_pivot" to "Enter digital freedom",
    "evt_erbolat_common_ending_stability_trigger_msg" to "The storms did not disappear, but businesses stopped drowning from each of them.",
    "evt_erbolat_common_ending_stability_trigger_opt_claim_stability" to "Establish a stable business",
    "evt_erbolat_common_ending_paycheck_trigger_msg" to "The company is still operating, but almost its entire purpose has gone into servicing obligations.",
    "evt_erbolat_common_ending_paycheck_trigger_opt_claim_paycheck" to "Recognize survival mode",
    "evt_dana_kz2005_burnout_label" to "After lessons, Dana’s voice trembles. She still smiles at the children, but at home she is silent longer than usual.",
    "evt_dana_kz2005_investment_label" to "The first conversations about savings sound almost awkward: in her world, money is usually either spent or hidden just in case.",
    "evt_dana_kz2015_burnout_label" to "The day is divided into roles without pauses: school, family, online students, anxiety about the course, anxiety about tomorrow.",
    "evt_dana_kz2015_investment_label" to "After the devaluation, Dana seriously understands for the first time that caution without knowledge does not always save money.",
    "evt_dana_kz2024_burnout_label" to "Even your favorite job begins to sound like a continuous background. Messages from student parents do not end with lessons.",
    "evt_dana_kz2024_investment_label" to "Dana gains a rare sense of control: she no longer just saves, but learns to make money part of a meaningful plan.",
    "evt_erbolat_kz2015_burnout_label" to "Erbolat stopped distinguishing between businesslike anger and fatigue. He comes home as if he were on a second shift, and not as if he were visiting his family.",
    "evt_erbolat_kz2015_finance_label" to "In 2015, for the first time he heard about tools that work not through “gut feeling,” but through discipline and structure.",
    "evt_erbolat_kz2024_burnout_label" to "Erbolat’s phone does not go silent, neither in the store, nor in the car, nor at night. Even success now comes in the form of notices and claims.",
    "evt_erbolat_kz2024_finance_label" to "Digital trading teaches him something painful, but important: intuition is no longer enough, a language of numbers and processes is needed.",
    "evt_aidar_2005_burnout_label" to "My eyes are red from old monitors, my head is noisy even after sleep. Aidar feels like he’s still sitting in front of the flickering screen, even when he’s driving home.",
    "evt_aidar_2005_investment_label" to "A colleague brings printouts about the first funds and bonds. It all looks boring next to the fast schemes, and that's why it suddenly seems reliable.",
    "evt_aidar_2015_burnout_label" to "Aidar notices that he no longer knows how to switch off. After work, he continues to live in tasks, messages and other people's deadlines.",
    "evt_aidar_2015_investment_label" to "After devaluation conversations and the first serious readings, he begins to distinguish an idea from a tool and a hype from a system.",
    "evt_aidar_2024_burnout_label" to "The morning begins not with cheerfulness, but with the desire to cancel the whole day. Slack blinks before he can even feel human.",
    "evt_aidar_2024_investment_label" to "Finally, the numbers are no longer just alarm. Aidar sees how knowledge transforms money from a source of stress into a manageable tool.",
